# Momento API - Identity

## Stack
Go 1.26.0 + MongoDB 8 + Swagger/OpenAPI

## Architecture
Clean Architecture + DDD (domain → app → ports ← adapters)
- **Dependency flow**: `ports → app → domain ← adapters`
SOLID + Object Calisthenics

## Task Routing
- **Architecture/structure**: @.cursor/rules/go_backend_architecture.md
- **Workflow/sequence**: @.cursor/rules/go_backend_workflow.md
- **Domain refactoring**: @.cursor/rules/go_backend_domain.md + @.cursor/rules/go_backend_object_calisthenics.md
- **Tests**: @.cursor/rules/go_backend_tests.md
- **Adapters**: @.cursor/rules/go_backend_adapters.md
- **App/services**: @.cursor/rules/go_backend_app.md
- **Handlers/routes**: @.cursor/rules/go_backend_ports.md
- **Style/conventions**: @.cursor/rules/go_backend_style.md

## Principles
- Logging only via HTTP middleware (pkg/nethttp)
- Context always 1st parameter
- Guard clauses (NO else)
- Errors: domain defines → app enriches → ports translates
- Tests: pragmatic coverage (80% target), see @.cursor/rules/go_backend_tests.md

## Structure
```
cmd/api/              # Orchestration
internal/{module}/    # domain → app → ports ← adapters
pkg/                  # Agnostic utilities
mocks/                # Generated by mockery
```

## Don't Do
- Log in domain/app/adapters
- Expose internal errors (500 = "internal server error")
- pkg import internal/

## Core Features
- Health check endpoint at `/health` (GET)
- Graceful shutdown with signal handling (SIGINT, SIGTERM)